# Optional web-app docroot for the self-host Caddy.
#
# Leave this empty to run engine-only (point the desktop app or a separately
# hosted web build at https://<your-domain>/engine). To serve the web app from
# the SAME domain, drop a production build here:
#
#   pnpm --filter houston-web build   # with VITE_NEW_ENGINE=1 (see ../README.md)
#   cp -r packages/web/dist/* selfhost/web/
#
# Caddy serves whatever is in this directory at https://<your-domain>/ and
# proxies the engine at https://<your-domain>/engine. This file just keeps the
# directory present in git so the compose bind-mount has something to mount.
